3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Firan-says-likely-to-hold-nuclear-talks-with-europeans-this-week%2Farticleshow%2F121161107.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Firan-says-likely-to-hold-nuclear-talks-with-europeans-this-week%2Famp_articleshow%2F121161107.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Firan-says-likely-to-hold-nuclear-talks-with-europeans-this-week%2Famp_articleshow%2F121161107.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Apple%20spent%20many%20years%20and%20billions%20of%20dollars%20investing%20in%20China.%20Now%20it's%20stuck%20there.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224859%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tim%20Cook%20at%20an%20Apple%20Store%20in%20Chengdu%2C%20China%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6823a82c3fe8d3928365bf8d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223340%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EApple%20CEO%20Tim%20Cook%20oversaw%20his%20company's%20deep%20investment%20in%20China.%20That%20was%20enormously%20successful%20strategy%20for%20Apple%20%E2%80%94%20but%20now%20it's%20a%20real%20problem%2C%20argues%20author%20Patrick%20McGee.%3Cp%3EVCG%2FVCG%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDonald%20Trump%20wants%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EApple%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20make%20iPhones%20in%20America.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThere's%20no%20chance%20that%20will%20happen%2C%20says%20Patrick%20McGee%2C%20a%20journalist%20who%20just%20published%20a%20book%20on%20Apple's%20deep%20ties%20to%20China.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMcGee%20also%20argues%20that%20Apple's%20end-around%20on%20Trump's%20China%20tariffs%20%E2%80%94%20saying%20that%20some%20iPhones%20and%20other%20products%20are%20made%20in%20India%20and%20Vietnam%20%E2%80%94%20is%20misleading.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20probably%20know%20that%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-iphone-mac-products-great-classic-boring-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EiPhone%2C%20and%20just%20about%20any%20other%20Apple%20product%3C%2Fa%3E%20you%20own%2C%20was%20made%20in%20China.%20And%20that%20Donald%20Trump%20wants%20Apple%20to%20move%20all%20of%20that%20production%20to%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20do%20you%20know%20how%2C%20and%20why%2C%20Apple%20ended%20up%20so%20dependent%20on%20China%20%E2%80%94%20and%20why%20that's%20so%20unlikely%20to%20change%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatrick%20McGee%20says%20he%20does.%20He's%20a%20journalist%20who%20just%20published%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.simonandschuster.com%2Fbooks%2FApple-in-China%2FPatrick-McGee%2F9781668053379%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple%20In%20China%3A%20The%20Capture%20of%20the%20World's%20Greatest%20Company%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20detailed%20look%20at%20all%20of%20the%20money%20and%20effort%20Apple%20spent%20over%20decades%20to%20enmesh%20itself%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcGee%2C%20who%20has%20covered%20Apple%20for%20the%20Financial%20Times%2C%20explains%20why%20this%20has%20been%20enormously%20helpful%20to%20Apple%20%E2%80%94%20because%20it%20created%20an%20ecosystem%20that%20lets%20it%20make%20ultra-complicated%20devices%20at%20vast%20scale.%20But%20he%20argues%20that%20it%20was%20even%20%3Cem%3Emore%3C%2Fem%3E%20helpful%20to%20China%20%E2%80%94%20because%20Apple%20gave%20Chinese%20engineers%20access%20to%20valuable%20technology%20that%20has%20let%20them%20build%20%3Cem%3Eother%3C%2Fem%3E%20high-value%20supply%20chains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20%3Cem%3Ethat%3C%2Fem%3E%20McGee%20posits%2C%20has%20created%20both%20a%20problem%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftim-cook%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EApple%20CEO%20Tim%20Cook%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20because%20he%20can%20no%20longer%20practically%20extract%20the%20company%20from%20China%20%E2%80%94%20and%20for%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20because%20its%20adversary%20is%20now%20using%20American%20know-how%20to%20compete%20with%20American%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(I%20asked%20Apple%20if%20it%20wanted%20to%20weigh%20in%20on%20McGee's%20book.%20Via%20a%20rep%2C%20the%20company%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bclaims%20in%20the%20book%20are%20untrue%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bfilled%20with%20inaccuracies%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20McGee%20didn't%20fact-check%20the%20book%20with%20Apple.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20talked%20to%20McGee%20for%20the%20newest%20episode%20of%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpodcasts.apple.com%2Fus%2Fpodcast%2Fchannels-with-peter-kafka%2Fid1080467174%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChannels%3C%2Fa%3E%20podcast.%20In%20the%20edited%20excerpt%20below%2C%20we%20talk%20about%20why%20he%20thinks%20it's%20impossible%20for%20Apple%20to%20move%20iPhone%20production%20to%20the%20US.%20And%20why%20McGee%20thinks%20that%20Apple%20saying%20it's%20moving%20some%20production%20to%20India%20and%20Vietnam%2C%20in%20order%20to%20escape%20some%20US%20tariffs%20on%20China%2C%20is%20deeply%20misleading.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeter%20Kafka%3A%20The%20Trump%20administration%20says%20it%20wants%20Apple%20to%20move%20all%20of%20its%20manufacturing%20to%20the%20US.%20You%20and%20anyone%20else%20who%20knows%20anything%20about%20Apple%20saying%20that%20is%20literally%20not%20possible%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20iPhone.%20Why%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatrick%20McGee%3A%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe're%20lacking%20so%20many%20things.%20The%20density%20of%20population%20is%20one.%20Lots%20of%20people%20know%20a%20factory%20town%20%5Bin%20China%5D%20might%20have%20500%2C000%20people%20just%20putting%20together%20the%20iPhone.%20The%20thing%20that%20people%20don't%20understand%20is%20they're%20not%20doing%20that%20year-round.%20They're%20doing%20that%20for%20three%20or%20four%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20they're%20moving%20on%20to%20another%20project.%20So%20Apple%20doesn't%20bear%20the%20cost.%20It's%20using%20the%20likes%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffoxconn-apple-largest-china-iphone-factory-sign-on-bonus-omicron-cny-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFoxconn%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20do%20manufacturing%20as%20a%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2025-04-11%2Fwhy-trump-s-dream-of-made-in-the-usa-iphones-isn-t-going-to-happen%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalyst%20quoted%20last%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20said%20it%20would%20be%20like%20if%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Boston%2C%20every%20person%20dropped%20what%20they%20were%20doing%20and%20just%20worked%20on%20iPhones.%20And%20as%20quotable%20as%20that%20is%2C%20that%20understates%20the%20challenge.%20Because%20it%20would%20like%20the%20city%20of%20Boston%20transporting%20itself%20to%20some%20other%20place%2C%20like%20Milwaukee%2C%20assembling%20iPhones%20for%20a%20few%20weeks%20and%20then%20moving%20on%20to%20some%20other%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20this%20floating%20population%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lensculture.com%2Farticles%2Fnadine-stijns-the-floating-population%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethat's%20literally%20what%20it's%20called%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20workforce%20alone%20is%20greater%20than%20America's%20entire%20labor%20force.%20So%20we're%20never%20going%20to%20match%20them%20in%20terms%20of%20density%20of%20population%20and%2C%20more%20especially%2C%20dynamism%20of%20the%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet%20alone%20that%20it's%20happening%20at%20way%20lower%20labor%20rates.%20Let%20alone%20it's%20got%20way%20better%20machinery%20and%20automation.%20It's%20not%20a%20matter%20of%20willpower%20and%20cost%20%E2%80%94%20that%20seems%20to%20be%20what%20the%20MAGA%20dream%20is%20based%20on.%20It%20goes%20so%20much%20beyond%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20often%20say%20Americans%20don't%20want%20to%20do%20these%20jobs.%20The%20%3Cem%3EChinese%3C%2Fem%3E%20don't%20want%20to%20do%20these%20jobs.%20But%20there%20are%20so%20many%20people%20that%20would%20rather%20be%20doing%20that%20than%20toiling%20in%20the%20fields%20for%2014%20hours%20a%20day.%20We%20just%20don't%20have%20a%20base%20of%20labor%20that%20would%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOne%20of%20the%20other%20arguments%20you%20and%20others%20make%20is%20that%20China%20has%20people%2C%20but%20there's%20also%20just%20huge%20infrastructure%3A%20a%20whole%20series%20of%20plants%20and%20subplants%20and%20subcontractors%20that%20all%20are%20sort%20of%20built%20around%20getting%20Apple%20the%20products%20it%20needs%2C%20at%20a%20drop%20of%20a%20hat.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYeah.%20In%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20that%20it%20would%20take%20China%20to%20build%20a%20new%20factory%2C%20we%20would%20still%20be%20doing%20the%20environmental%20paperwork.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20in%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Daeedf455f6d638248b977217f27893d52de9b23258fd1ba871d8ede9749b42a5%26postID%3D682397d6b2c932bc4b8d9b9b%26postSlug%3Dapple-china-tariff-supply-chain-book-patrick-mcgee-peter-kafka-2025-05%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.apple.com%252Finvestor%252Fearnings-call%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EApple's%20most%20recent%20earnings%20call%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%2C%20the%20company%20said%20that%20for%20the%20next%20quarter%20at%20least%2C%20every%20iPhone%20they%20sell%20in%20the%20US%20is%20going%20to%20come%20out%20of%20India%2C%20and%20most%20of%20the%20other%20electronics%20they%20sell%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20AirPods%2C%20etc%20%E2%80%94%20are%20going%20to%20come%20out%20of%20Vietnam.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20what%20am%20I%20missing%20here%3F%20It%20makes%20it%20seem%20like%20Apple%20%3Cem%3Ehas%3C%2Fem%3E%20gone%20ahead%20and%20figured%20out%20how%20to%20move%20this%20stuff%20out%20of%20China.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20at%20all.%20Think%20of%20it%20like%20this%3A%20If%20there's%20a%20thousand%20steps%20in%20making%20an%20iPhone%20and%20the%20final%20one%20is%20now%20in%20India%2C%20you're%20avoiding%20tariffs.%20The%20final%20assembly%20is%20considered%20%26quot%3Bmaking%20it%20in%20India.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELike%20if%20I%20took%20every%20step%20of%20baking%20a%20cake%20except%20for%20putting%20the%20icing%20on%20or%20...%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPutting%20it%20in%20the%20box%20or%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHonestly%2C%20not%20much%20is%20happening%20in%20India.%20That%20might%20change%20in%20the%20next%20five%20to%2010%20years%2C%20but%20the%20idea%20that%20there%20is%20actual%20production%20happening%20in%20India%20is%20just%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20buy%20an%20iPhone%20next%20year%2C%20it'll%20say%20%26quot%3Bmade%20in%20India.%26quot%3B%20I%20think%20that's%20a%20near-certainty.%20But%20that%20phone%20will%20be%20no%20less%20dependent%20on%20the%20China-centric%20supply%20chain%20than%20any%20other%20iPhone%20you've%20ever%20purchased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20that%20earnings%20call%2C%20Apple%20also%20said%20that%20the%20existing%20tariffs%20will%20cost%20them%20%24900%20million%20in%20the%20next%20quarter.%20That%20may%20sound%20like%20a%20big%20number%2C%20but%20Apple%20makes%20%24100%20billion%20in%20profit%20a%20year%2C%20so%20it's%20not.%20If%20that%20was%20just%20the%20only%20impact%20from%20the%20tariffs%2C%20that%20seems%20like%20a%20pretty%20solvable%20problem%20for%20Apple%3A%20They%20have%20to%20move%20final%20assembly%20to%20India%2C%20and%20eat%20some%20costs%2C%20but%20they%20could%20do%20it.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYeah%2C%20absolutely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhere%20I%20think%20things%20are%20much%20dicier%20is%20that%20the%20political%20ties%20that%20Apple%20has%20with%20China%20are%20unbreakable.%20I%20shouldn't%20say%20political%20ties%20%E2%80%94%20I%20really%20mean%20the%20business%20ties.%20They%20are%20not%20going%20to%20leave%20China%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20technological%20transfer%20that%20is%20engendered%20by%20designing%20cutting-edge%20products%20every%20year%20and%20building%20them%20in%20China%20inherently%20causes%20a%20technology%20transfer%20from%20America%20to%20China%20on%20a%20crazy%20level.%20And%20if%20you%20think%20of%20China%20as%20a%20threat%2C%20if%20you%20think%20of%20them%20as%20America's%20biggest%20adversary%2C%20it%20is%20insane%20that%20the%20world's%20greatest%20company%20is%20equipping%20China%20with%20this%20technological%20know-how%20year%20in%2C%20year%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Ftech%2Fapple-iphone-price-increase-2eaebb14%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20just%20reported%20that%20Apple%20is%20thinking%20about%20maybe%20tacking%20on%20some%20of%20these%20additional%20costs%20to%20the%20next%20round%20of%20iPhones%20they%20start%20selling%20this%20fall%20%E2%80%94%20passing%20those%20costs%20on%20to%20the%20consumer.%20Does%20that%20sound%20right%20to%20you%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20because%20the%20other%20alternative%20is%20that%20you're%20squeezing%20out%20more%20from%20your%20suppliers.%20Some%20analysts%20have%20suggested%20that%2C%20and%20it's%20kind%20of%20laughable.%20Because%20if%20there's%20anything%20to%20squeeze%20out%20of%20the%20supply%20chain%2C%20you%20damn%20well%20better%20know%20that%20Apple's%20already%20done%20it.%20Apple%20pays%20its%20suppliers%20very%20slim%20margins.%20There%20are%20not%20a%20bunch%20of%20fat%20cats%20out%20there%20that%20they%20can%20just%20be%20squeezing%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-china-tariff-supply-chain-book-patrick-mcgee-peter-kafka-2025-05%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747216861000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6823b2553fe8d3928365c1f2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-china-tariff-supply-chain-book-patrick-mcgee-peter-kafka-2025-05%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Donald%20Trump%20wants%20Apple%20to%20make%20iPhones%20in%20the%20US.%20That%20won't%20happen%2C%20says%20journalist%20Patrick%20McGee%2C%20who%20just%20wrote%20a%20book%20on%20Apple's%20ties%20to%20China.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22pkafka%40insider.com%20(Peter%20Kafka)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A88%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-china-tariff-supply-chain-book-patrick-mcgee-peter-kafka-2025-05%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%201%20Bengaluru%20Startup%20Is%20Earning%20Rs%205.2%20Crore%20While%20Tackling%20Plastic%20Waste%20in%20Food%20Packaging%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EYou%20run%20a%20food%20business%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20caf%C3%A9%2C%20cloud%20kitchen%2C%20or%20restaurant%20chain%20%E2%80%94%20and%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20packaging%2C%20a%20few%20things%20matter%20most%3A%20It%20should%20%3Cstrong%3Eretain%20heat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20%3Cstrong%3Enot%20leak%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20and%20r%3Cstrong%3Eeach%20your%20customer%20intact%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20why%20plastic%20has%20become%20the%20go-to.%20It%E2%80%99s%20cheap%2C%20it%20works%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20have%20you%20paused%20to%20consider%20the%20environmental%20cost%20of%20every%20plastic%20lid%2C%20bowl%2C%20and%20box%20you%20send%20out%20the%20door%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%