he%20doldrums%2C%20according%20to%20Chen%20Zhao%2C%20the%20head%20of%20economic%20research%20at%20Redfin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20direction%20of%20mortgage%20rates%20depends%20heavily%20on%20whether%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-powell-interest-rates-tariffs-inflation-economy-stagflation-federal-reserve-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFederal%20Reserve%3C%2Fa%3E%20cuts%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20the%20central%20bank%20is%20not%20expected%20to%20slash%20its%20benchmark%20rate%20until%20September.%20%26quot%3BWe%20think%20we're%20in%20the%20right%20place%20to%20wait%20and%20see%20how%20things%20evolve%2C%26quot%3B%20Fed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20said%20at%20the%20May%20FOMC%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPotential%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-april-cpi-tariffs-prices-trump-trade-war-economci-outlook-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einflationary%20effects%20from%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20why%20the%20Fed%20is%20dragging%20its%20feet%20on%20rate%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20inflation%20rate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-april-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20April%3C%2Fa%3E%20came%20out%20to%202.3%25%20year-over-year%2C%20down%20from%202.4%25%20the%20previous%20month.%20However%2C%20it's%20likely%20that%20the%20full%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-april-cpi-tariffs-prices-trump-trade-war-economci-outlook-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpacts%20of%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20haven't%20worked%20their%20way%20through%20the%20data%20yet.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Feconres%2Fnotes%2Ffeds-notes%2Fdetecting-tariff-effects-on-consumer-prices-in-real-time-20250509.html%3Futm_source%3Dsubstack%26utm_medium%3Demail%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Fed%2C%20inflation%20from%20the%20trade%20war%20could%20take%20two%20months%20to%20materialize%20into%20price%20increases%20for%20consumers.%20Prolonged%20inflation%20uncertainty%20means%20the%20Fed%20will%20be%20hesitant%20to%20make%20a%20move%20to%20cut%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrade%20talks%20with%20China%20are%20a%20big%20contributing%20factor%20to%20the%20Fed's%20inflation%20outlook%2C%20according%20to%20Zhao.%20Tariffs%20on%20China%20have%20been%20reduced%20from%20145%25%20to%2030%25%2C%20easing%20trade%20tensions%20but%20still%20contributing%20to%20inflation%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227af46387-40a5-4375-8858-ef7622a04668%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERecession%20risk%20is%20still%20here%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHigher%20mortgage%20rates%20aren't%20all%20bad%3A%20in%20one%20sense%2C%20they're%20a%20sign%20that%20the%20labor%20market%20is%20strong%20enough%20to%20support%20elevated%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Zhao%2C%20there%20is%20still%20one%20scenario%20where%20mortgage%20rates%20could%20drop%3A%20if%20a%20recession%20eventually%20unfolds.%20And%20that's%20a%20real%20possibility%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20asked%20me%20two%20or%20three%20months%20ago%2C%20I%20would%20have%20said%20mortgage%20rates%20are%20probably%20going%20to%20stay%20around%20this%20level%20for%20a%20while.%20But%20now%20with%20the%20introduction%20of%20tariffs%2C%20it's%20definitely%20a%20lot%20more%20uncertain%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20told%20BI%20in%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wouldn't%20say%20it's%20like%20the%20base%20case%20scenario%2C%20but%20it's%20definitely%20possible%20that%20you%20can%20get%20a%20pretty%20severe%20recession.%20In%20that%20case%2C%20the%20recession%20takes%20care%20of%20the%20inflation%20risk%2C%20and%20you%20could%20see%20mortgage%20rates%20falling%20to%20where%20they%20were%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETariff%20levels%20have%20receded%20from%20the%20panic-inducing%20levels%20they%20were%20at%20earlier%2C%20but%20they're%20still%20high%20enough%20to%20drag%20on%20growth.%20After%20talks%20with%20China%2C%20the%20average%20US%20tariff%20rate%20has%20dropped%20from%2023%25%20to%2015%25%2C%20but%20that's%20still%20much%20higher%20than%20the%202.5%25%20rate%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20economic%20data%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20sharply%20worsens%20or%20trade%20war%20tensions%20flare%20up%20again%2C%20then%20that%20could%20provide%20the%20Fed%20with%20a%20reason%20to%20cut.%20But%20in%20that%20case%2C%20lower%20mortgage%20rates%20wouldn't%20offer%20much%20relief%20for%20homebuyers%2C%20as%20a%20recession%20would%20come%20with%20elevated%20unemployment%20rates%20and%20weakening%20household%20balance%20sheets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLooking%20ahead%2C%20with%20the%20dual%20risk%20of%20higher%20inflation%20and%20unemployment%20putting%20the%20Fed%20in%20a%20bind%2C%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20imagine%20any%20relief%20for%20mortgage%20rates%20without%20a%20fairly%20severe%20recession%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20wrote%20in%20a%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmortgage-rates-forecast-remain-high-unless-economic-recession-fed-redfin-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747211401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6823aecc3fe8d3928365c12e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmortgage-rates-forecast-remain-high-unless-economic-recession-fed-redfin-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Homebuyers%20shouldn't%20hold%20out%20for%20mortgage%20rate%20relief%2C%20according%20to%20Chen%20Zhao%2C%20Redfin's%20economic%20lead.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cji%40businessinsider.com%20(Christine%20Ji)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A80%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2