2Fjep.37.4.23%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E8%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20their%20salary%20%E2%80%94%20a%20number%20that%20may%20be%20as%20high%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw33383%2Fw33383.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E25%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20tech%20workers.%20If%20your%20business%20isn't%20doing%20well%2C%20or%20if%20you%20need%20to%20reallocate%20head%20count%20among%20departments%2C%20it%20makes%20sense%20to%20%3Cem%3Eforce%3C%2Fem%3E%20some%20attrition%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20during%20a%20period%20of%20economic%20uncertainty%2C%20when%20virtually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-stuck-job-search-hiring-work-trump-tariffs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eno%20one%20is%20quitting%3C%2Fa%3E%20their%20job.%20By%20pushing%20employees%20to%20leave%20voluntarily%2C%20employers%20reduce%20their%20payroll%20without%20having%20to%20provide%20the%20departing%20workers%20with%20severance%20or%20health%20insurance.%20It's%20layoffs%20on%20the%20cheap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20RTO%20push%20isn't%20just%20financial.%20Bosses%20want%20to%20go%20back%20to%20happier%20pre-pandemic%20times%20when%20everyone%20was%20in%20the%20office%20all%20the%20time%2C%20even%20if%20that%20means%20losing%20a%20few%20stars%20in%20the%20process.%20They%20think%20employees%20will%20be%20more%20productive%20under%20the%20watchful%20gaze%20of%20their%20managers.%20They%20think%20teams%20will%20get%20along%20better%20by%20seeing%20one%20another%20in%20person.%20They%20think%20that%20their%20new%20grads%20will%20learn%20faster%20by%20overhearing%20the%20conversations%20of%20their%20mentors%2C%20and%20that%20people%20from%20different%20teams%20will%20run%20into%20one%20another%20around%20the%20watercooler%20and%20come%20up%20with%20the%20next%20breakthrough%20idea.%20The%20more%20of%20that%2C%20the%20better%2C%20they%20think%20%E2%80%94%20and%20soon%20even%20the%20reluctant%20workers%20will%20realize%20this%20was%20the%20better%20way%20all%20along%2C%20so%20best%20just%20to%20eliminate%20work-from-home%20days%20altogether.%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20look%20just%20like%20it%20did%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20JPMorgan%20CEO%20Jamie%20Dimon%20explained%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20everyone's%20going%20to%20be%20happy%20with%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20companies%20see%20an%20upside%2C%20both%20financial%20and%20cultural%2C%20in%20putting%20an%20end%20to%20hybrid%20work.%20And%20they're%20gambling%20that%20in%20the%20current%20job%20market%2C%20most%20employees%20will%20have%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20come%20into%20the%20office%20as%20ordered.%20Sure%2C%20some%20people%20will%20grumble%20about%20losing%20their%20work-from-home%20lifestyles.%20And%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-changing-rto-pay-performance-reviws-want-you-to-quit-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esome%20may%20even%20quit%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20in%20a%20time%20of%20corporate%20contraction%2C%20that%20can%20seem%20like%20a%20%3Cem%3Egood%20%3C%2Fem%3Ething.%20When%20you're%20trying%20to%20slash%20your%20workforce%20by%2020%25%2C%20every%20employee%20who%20leaves%20is%20one%20fewer%20employee%20you%20have%20to%20lay%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20current%20state%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-collar-recession-hiring-slump-jobs-tech-industry-applications-rejection-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20their%20gamble%20might%20well%20pay%20off.%20But%20I%20think%20employers%20may%20be%20underestimating%20the%20downsides%20of%20RTO%20mandates.%20For%20starters%2C%20spurring%20a%20voluntary%20exodus%20gives%20companies%20no%20control%20over%20%3Cem%3Ehow%20many%3C%2Fem%3E%20employees%20will%20quit.%20That%20means%20they%20could%20end%20up%20overshooting%20their%20target%3A%20When%20the%20dating%20app%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrindr-loses-employees-after-rto-ultimatum-office-relocation-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGrindr%20revoked%20its%20work-from-home%3C%2Fa%3E%20policy%20in%202023%2C%20nearly%20%3Cem%3Ehalf%3C%2Fem%3E%20its%20workforce%20resigned.%20That%20kind%20of%20wholesale%20flight%20is%20unlikely%20in%20the%20current%20job%20market%2C%20but%20it%20underscores%20the%20risk%20of%20rolling%20the%20dice%20with%20an%20RTO%20mandate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20more%20importantly%2C%20companies%20can't%20control%20%3Cem%3Ewho%3C%2Fem%3E%20decides%20to%20leave.%20Researchers%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fharris.uchicago.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fwright-return-to-office.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudied%20the%20effects%20of%20RTO%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Apple%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20SpaceX%20found%20that%20the%20companies%20lost%20more%20senior%20employees%20than%20low-level%20workers.%20And%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D5031481%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20broader%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20companies%20in%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%2C%20researchers%20found%20that%20employers%20also%20lost%20some%20of%20their%20most%20skilled%20employees.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20going%20to%20get%20negative%20selection%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Nick%20Bloom%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Stanford%20who%20studies%20remote%20work.%20%26quot%3BThe%20ones%20who%20leave%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20can%20pull%20an%20outside%20offer%2C%20who%20are%20the%20better%20employees.%26quot%3B%20Yes%2C%20the%20rocky%20state%20of%20the%20job%20market%20will%20prevent%20most%20employees%20from%20jumping%20ship.%20But%20the%20best%20of%20the%20best%20will%20always%20be%20in%20demand.%20That's%20especially%20the%20case%20right%20now%20for%20AI%20specialists%2C%20who%20are%20the%20very%20workers%20businesses%20can%20least%20afford%20to%20lose%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-openai-anthropic-ai-agents-training-data-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20AI%20wars%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Ordering%20people%20back%20to%20the%20office%20means%20you'll%20lose%20some%20of%20your%20best%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20employers%20are%20getting%20around%20the%20brain%20drain%20by%20quietly%20exempting%20their%20mission-critical%20employees%20from%20the%20RTO%20mandates.%20Sometimes%20these%20exemptions%20are%20official%2C%20covering%20entire%20teams%20assigned%20to%20high-priority%20projects%20or%20individual%20hotshots%20the%20company%20doesn't%20want%20to%20lose%20to%20a%20competitor.%20But%20in%20many%20cases%2C%20the%20exemptions%20are%20unofficial%3A%20a%20middle%20manager%2C%20say%2C%20who%20looks%20the%20other%20way%20when%20high%20performers%20don't%20come%20into%20the%20office%20every%20day.%20Either%20way%2C%20exemptions%20foster%20a%20sense%20of%20inequality%2C%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20resentment%20among%20employees%20who%20feel%20they're%20being%20treated%20unfairly.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4675401%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20job%20satisfaction%20ratings%20declined%20significantly%20post-RTO%20%E2%80%94%20and%20unhappy%20employees%20make%20for%20unproductive%20ones.%20Companies%20might%20think%20that%20ordering%20everyone%20back%20to%20the%20office%20will%20foster%20an%20%3Cem%3Eesprit%20de%20corps%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20spur%20everyone%20to%20greater%20heights%20of%20creativity%20and%20innovation.%20But%20the%20data%20suggests%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20companies%20that%20adopt%20a%20take-it-or-leave-it%20attitude%20over%20RTO%20can%20wind%20up%20getting%20the%20worst%20of%20both%20worlds.%20They%20lose%20their%20top%20talent%20while%20retaining%20their%20average%20and%20low%20performers%20%E2%80%94%20employees%20whose%20performance%20will%20likely%20dip%20even%20lower%20in%20the%20post-RTO%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20let's%20assume%20that%20the%20CEOs%20who%20are%20implementing%20RTO%20mandates%20are%20aware%20of%20the%20risk%20they're%20taking.%20So%20why%20don't%20they%20just%20do%20things%20the%20old-fashioned%20way%20and%20lay%20people%20off%2C%20instead%20of%20trying%20to%20force%20them%20to%20leave%3F%20By%20choosing%20whom%20to%20fire%2C%20they%20could%20keep%20their%20best%20employees%20and%20let%20their%20mediocre%20ones%20go.%20That's%20what%20companies%20like%20Microsoft%20and%20Meta%20are%20doing%3A%20aggressively%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flow-performer-layoffs-firings-elon-musk-mark-zuckerberg-management-tech-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaying%20off%20those%20they%20view%20as%20low%20performers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20make%20room%20in%20their%20budgets%20to%20hire%20more%20AI%20engineers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20layoffs%20also%20come%20with%20a%20significant%20downside.%20Studies%20show%20they%20create%20a%20culture%20of%20fear%2C%20which%20affects%20the%20productivity%20and%20performance%20of%20the%20employees%20who%20survive%20%E2%80%94%20perhaps%20even%20as%20much%20as%20an%20RTO%20mandate%20would.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20making%20cuts%20to%20their%20workforces%2C%20employers%20are%20going%20to%20pay%20a%20price%20no%20matter%20how%20they%20go%20about%20it.%20The%20question%20is%3A%20What's%20the%20best%20way%20to%20mitigate%20the%20negative%20consequences%20in%20the%20current%20environment%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20five%20years%2C%20an%20army%20of%20economists%2C%20organizational%20psychologists%2C%20and%20management%20scholars%20has%20scrutinized%20every%20aspect%20of%20our%20great%20work-from-home%20experiment.%20Their%20conclusion%20is%20unequivocal%3A%20By%20almost%20any%20metric%2C%20hybrid%20work%20works.%20It%20boosts%20employee%20engagement%2C%20maintains%20productivity%2C%20and%20engenders%20loyalty%20and%20retention%20among%20high%20performers.%20So%20one%20answer%20for%20companies%20that%20need%20to%20cut%20their%20workforce%20might%20be%20to%20zig%20when%20everyone%20else%20is%20zagging.%20By%20limiting%20RTO%20to%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20say%2C%20instead%20of%20four%2C%20companies%20can%20hold%20on%20to%20more%20of%20their%20superstars%20than%20their%20corporate%20rivals%2C%20while%20still%20enjoying%20the%20benefits%20of%20in-person%20collaboration.%20Yes%2C%20they%20might%20have%20to%20increase%20layoffs%20in%20the%20short%20run.%20But%20when%20the%20economy%20rebounds%2C%20as%20it%20eventually%20will%2C%20they'll%20be%20better%20positioned%20to%20expand.%20By%20bucking%20the%20trend%2C%20companies%20can%20stand%20out%20from%20the%20crowd.%20And%20in%20a%20crowded%20market%2C%20being%20a%20standout%20is%20exactly%20where%20you%20want%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faki-ito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAki%20Ito%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-mandates-layoffs-quit-jobs-hybrid-remote-work-office-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747211341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682390fe68a292900801329f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-mandates-layoffs-quit-jobs-hybrid-remote-work-office-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cynics%20suspect%20that%20RTO%20mandates%20are%20actually%20a%20sneaky%20substitute%20for%20layoffs.%20It%20looks%20like%20they%20may%20be%20right.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aito%40businessinsider.com%20(Aki%20Ito)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A38%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-mandates-layoffs-quit-jobs-hybrid-remote-work-office-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80